Last year, people aged 60 and over made up nearly 22 percent of the Shanghai registered population, while the birth rate was less than one child per couple.
Xie Lingli, director of Shanghai City Commission on Population and Family Planning said many couples must have children to "help reduce the proportion of the aging population and reduce the workforce in the future".
