I hope that your country will soon be recognized by the United Nations, said Alexei Ostrovsky, a member of the Russian parliament and drank a glass of vodka on it.
The opposition, which was represented in the election by former vice-president Raul Khadzhimba and two businessmen Zaus Ardzinba and Beslan Boutba, has criticized contracts made with Moscow last year, such as a contract that allows Russia to control the Abkhazian rail network for 10 years.
The fifth candidate, Vitali Bganba, says he does not support either the current government or the opposition.
A majority of 50% plus one vote is required to win the election.
If none of the candidates achieves this result, the decisive duel must take place within two weeks.
